---

# Failure Conditions

Reject the workflow if:

Research was skipped.

Customer psychology was ignored.

No positioning exists.

No hypothesis exists.

No prioritization exists.

No testing plan exists.

No recommendation exists.

No knowledge capture exists.

Restart from the missing phase.

---

# Success Criteria

A successful workflow ensures that every project:

Reduces uncertainty.

Improves decision quality.

Produces reusable knowledge.

Generates testable hypotheses.

Delivers production-ready strategy.

Creates a repeatable competitive advantage.

Only then is the workflow considered complete.
